INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (2,1,'2009-11-13 14:07:02','2009-11-13 14:07:02','This is my web development learning journal. It\'s a place for me to store useful code and information that I work with so I can refer back to it in the future. It\'s also a learning tool because writing down a problem or solution makes me think about it logically and helps me to understand it.\r\n\r\nI\'m a web developer and I work at <a title=\"The Cubeworks site\" href=\"http://www.cubeworks.co.uk\">Cubeworks </a>in <a title=\"Brighton on the map\" href=\"http://maps.google.co.uk/maps?f=q&amp;source=s_q&amp;hl=en&amp;geocode=&amp;q=brighton,+uk&amp;sll=53.800651,-4.064941&amp;sspn=20.824402,57.084961&amp;ie=UTF8&amp;hq=&amp;hnear=Brighton,+East+Sussex,+United+Kingdom&amp;ll=50.819818,-0.131836&amp;spn=22.241089,57.084961&amp;z=5\">Brighton</a>.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-292\" title=\"Jonathan Sewell\" src=\"http://www.jonathansewell.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2009/11/DSCF3927_small.jpg\" alt=\"Jonathan Sewell\" width=\"300\" height=\"300\" />','About','','publish','open','open','','about','','','2010-11-29 20:19:50','2010-11-29 20:19:50','',0,'http://localhost/?page_id=2',0,'page','',0),(3,1,'2009-11-17 14:02:22','2009-11-17 14:02:22','I\'ve just spent a lunch break getting a Wordpress site up and running for my blog. I was pleasantly surprised at how easy it is to set up. The Wordpress <a title=\"Wordpress installation instructions\" href=\"http://codex.wordpress.org/Installing_WordPress#Famous_5-Minute_Install\">Famous 5-Minute Install</a> documentation set it out very clearly.\r\n\r\nHere\'s what I did:\r\n\r\nInstalled PHP on my development machine with IIS7 (probably the trickiest part)\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a title=\"PHP documentation\" href=\"http://www.php.net/manual/en/install.windows.iis7.php\">Enable FastCGI support in IIS7</a></li>\r\n	<li>Created an IIS7 website, unzip Wordpress site there</li>\r\n	<li>Installed MySQL and MySQL Administrator (part of the MySQL Tools download) from <a title=\"MySQL Downloads\" href=\"http://dev.mysql.com/downloads/\">the MySQL site</a></li>\r\n	<li>Used MySQL Administrator to created a new MySQL database and a new user for that database</li>\r\n	<li>Edit wp-config.php in the Wordpress site<a title=\"wp-config.php settings\" href=\"http://codex.wordpress.org/Installing_WordPress#Step_3:_Set_up_wp-config.php\"> to point to your database</a></li>\r\n	<li>Browse to the installation page and it\'s as easy as that</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nNext, I created a MySQL database on my hosting provider and uploaded the website to the web server, changing the wp-config.php file to point to the new database.\r\n\r\nI did have to edit the database table wp_options to update the URL of the website because it was going to http://localhost when I tried to go to the admin pages.','Wordpress in a lunch break','','draft','open','open','','wordpress-in-a-lunch-break','','','2010-06-29 14:27:30','2010-06-29 13:27:30','',0,'http://blog.jonathansewell.co.uk.temp.realssl.com/?p=3',0,'post','',0),(4,1,'2009-11-17 14:01:40','2009-11-17 14:01:40','I\'ve just spent a lunch break getting a Wordpress site up and running for my blog. I was pleasantly surprised at how easy it is to set up. The Wordpress <a title=\"Wordpress installation instructions\" href=\"http://codex.wordpress.org/Installing_WordPress#Famous_5-Minute_Install\" target=\"_blank\">Famous 5-Minute Install</a> documentation set it out very clearly.\n\nHere\'s what I did:\n\nInstalled PHP on my development machine with IIS7 (probably the trickiest part)\n<ul>\n	<li><a title=\"PHP documentation\" href=\"http://www.php.net/manual/en/install.windows.iis7.php\" target=\"_blank\">Enable FastCGI support in IIS7</a></li>\n	<li>Created an IIS7 website, unzip Wordpress site there</li>\n	<li>Installed MySQL and MySQL Administrator (part of the MySQL Tools download) from <a title=\"MySQL Downloads\" href=\"http://dev.mysql.com/downloads/\" target=\"_blank\">the MySQL site</a