st reading entities from the repository into the model\n<ul>\n	<li>Test for when repositoryÂ returns null</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n	<li>Creating entities\n<ul>\n	<li>Check that all model values are passed to the repository method</li>\n	<li>Check PRG pattern used</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n	<li>Editing entities\n<ul>\n	<li>Test model is populated from repository</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n	<li>Updating entities\n<ul>\n	<li>Check that all model values are passed to the repository method</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n	<li>Deleting entries\n<ul>\n	<li>Check that all model values are passed to the repository method</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\nCheck out \"all controller test\"','','','inherit','open','open','','104-revision-4','','','2010-05-14 12:27:17','2010-05-14 11:27:17','',104,'http://www.jonathansewell.co.uk/index.php/2010/05/14/104-revision-4/',0,'revision','',0),(109,1,'2010-05-06 17:38:35','2010-05-06 16:38:35','EPiServer stores language resources in XML file sin the \"lang\" folder of the site.\r\n<blockquote>At startup, your EPiServer site will load all the .xml files in the ~/lang directory, alphabetically. A DOM of all language resources will be built in memory, adding all elements from each .xml file, and then cached for the rest of the application life-time (if you change one of the files, it will automatically trigger a reload.) <em>Source: </em><a href=\"http://labs.episerver.com/en/Blogs/Steve-Celius/Dates/112266/112267/Compare-and-keep-language-files-in-sync/\"><em>http://labs.episerver.com/en/Blogs/Steve-Celius/Dates/112266/112267/Compare-and-keep-language-files-in-sync/</em></a></blockquote>\r\nThis means you can add your own XMLÂ languageÂ resources for things like control labels on your templates. It is best practice to leave the EPiServer langauge files intact and create your own files.\r\n\r\nIf you need to override an existing element you can do so, this works particularly well because all the XML files are loaded into a DOM, and any existing elements are overwritten by the later element (alphabetically).\r\n\r\nTo avoid conflicts with existing language files you could simply create a new XML element to contain your translations, for example:\r\n<pre class=\"brush:csharp\">&lt;language name=\"English\" id=\"EN\"&gt;\r\n      &lt;mywebsitename&gt;\r\n           &lt;home&gt;Home in English&lt;/home&gt;\r\n      &lt;/mywebsitename&gt;\r\n &lt;/language&gt;</pre>\r\n<strong>Accessing Translations</strong>\r\n\r\nCalling Translate:\r\n<pre class=\"brush:csharp\">LanguageManager.Instance.Translate(\"/standard/home\")</pre>\r\nFor the XML:\r\n<pre class=\"brush:csharp\">&lt;language name=\"English\" id=\"EN\"&gt;\r\n      &lt;standard&gt;\r\n           &lt;home&gt;Home in English&lt;/home&gt;\r\n      &lt;/standard&gt;\r\n &lt;/language&gt;</pre>\r\nThis will output the string \"Home in English\" if the current culture is English.\r\n\r\n<strong>References</strong>\r\n<a href=\"http://labs.episerver.com/en/Blogs/Steve-Celius/Dates/112266/112267/Compare-and-keep-language-files-in-sync/\">http://labs.episerver.com/en/Blogs/Steve-Celius/Dates/112266/112267/Compare-and-keep-language-files-in-sync/</a>\r\n<a href=\"http://danielsaidi.wordpress.com/tag/episerver/\">http://danielsaidi.wordpress.com/tag/episerver/</a>','EPiServer Translate and XML','','inherit','open','open','','95-revision-5','','','2010-05-06 17:38:35','2010-05-06 16:38:35','',95,'http://www.jonathansewell.co.uk/index.php/2010/05/06/95-revision-5/',0,'revision','',0),(110,1,'2010-05-06 16:56:06','2010-05-06 15:56:06','<strong>Get the start page PageReference:</strong>\r\n<pre class=\"brush:csharp\">PageReference.StartPage</pre>\r\nA PageRefernce is basically a wrapper for integer ids. It also containsÂ convenienceÂ methods as in the above example which simply gets the start page id from the configuration:\r\n<pre class=\"brush:csharp\">EPiServer.Configuration.Settings.Instance.PageStartId</pre>\r\nThe PageData class holds information about the page such as name and URL. It makes pageÂ propertiesÂ available through the property \"Property\" (PropertyDataCollection).\r\n\r\n<strong>Get PageData from a PageReference:</strong>\r\n<pre class=\"brush:csharp\">DataFactory.Instance.GetPage(PageReference.StartPage)</pre>','EPiServer Snippets','','inherit','open','open','','89-revision-5','','','2010-05-06 16:56:06','2010-05-06 15:56:06','',89,'http://www.jonathansewell.co.uk/index.php/2010/05/06/89-revision-5/',0,'revision','',0),(111,1,'2010-05-01 11:03:28','2010-05-01 10:03:28','<pre class=\"brush:csharp\">var minutesRegex = /\\d+(?=m)/;\r\nvar minutesMatch = minutesRegex.exec(timeString)\r\n\r\nif (minutesMatch) {\r\n	var minutes = minutesMatch[0];\r\n}</pre>\r\n<h3>The regular expression</h3>\r\n\\d matches any digit\r\n\r\n+ matches one or more\r\n\r\n(?=m) is a zero-width positive lookahead, it matches \"m\" but doesn\'t include it in the result of the match eg. t(?=s) matches the secondÂ t inÂ streets (<a href=\"http://www.regular-expressions.info/refadv.html\">http://www.regular-expressions.info/refadv.html</a>). It will match \"10\" in the string \"2h 10m 30s\"\r\n\r\n<h3>References</h3>\r\n<a href=\"http://www.regular-expressions.info/javascript.html\">http://www.regular-expressions.info/javascript.html</a>','Javascript Regex','','inherit','open','open','','75-revision-8','','','2010-05-01 11:03:28','2010-05-01 10:03:28','',75,'http://www.jonathansewell.co.uk/index.php/2010/05/01/75-revision-8/',0,'revision','',0),(112,1,'2010-05-15 23:14:27','2010-05-15 22:14:27','<pre class=\"brush:csharp\">var minutesRegex = /\\d+(?=m)/;\r\nvar minutesMatch = minutesRegex.exec(timeString)\r\n\r\nif (minutesMatch) {\r\n	var minutes = minutesMatch[0];\r\n}</pre>\r\n<h3>The regular expression</h3>\r\n\\d matches any digit\r\n\r\n+ matches one or more\r\n\r\n(?=m) is a zero-width positive lookahead, it matches \"m\" but doesn\'t include it in the result of the match eg. t(?=s) matches the secondÂ t inÂ streets (<a href=\"http://www.regular-expressions.info/refadv.html\">http://www.regular-expressions.info/refadv.html</a>). It will match \"10\" in the string \"2h 10m 30s\"\r\n<h3>References</h3>\r\n<a href=\"http://www.regular-expressions.info/javascript.html\">http://www.regular-expressions.info/javascript.html</a>','Javascript Minute Regex','An example and explaination of a zero-width positive lookahead regex in JavaScript','inherit','open','open','','75-revision-9','','','2010-05-15 23:14:27','2010-05-15 22:14:27','',75,'http://www.jonathansewell.co.uk/index.php/2010/05/15/75-revision-9/',0,'revision','',0),(113,1,'2010-05-15 23:14:50','2010-05-15 22:14:50','<pre class=\"brush:csharp\">var minutesRegex = /\\d+(?=m)/;\r\nvar minutesMatch = minutesRegex.exec(timeString)\r\n\r\nif (minutesMatch) {\r\n	var minutes = minutesMatch[0];\r\n}</pre>\r\n<h3>The regular expression</h3>\r\n\\d matches any digit\r\n\r\n+ matches one or more\r\n\r\n(?=m) is a zero-width positive lookahead, it matches \"m\" but doesn\'t include it in the result of the match eg. t(?=s) matches the secondÂ t inÂ streets (<a href=\"http://www.regular-expressions.info/refadv.html\">http://www.regular-expressions.info/refadv.html</a>). It will match \"10\" in the string \"2h 10m 30s\"\r\n<h3>References</h3>\r\n<a href=\"http://www.regular-expressions.info/javascript.html\">http://www.regular-expressions.info/javascript.html</a>','Javascript Regex \\d+(?=m)','An example and explaination of a zero-width positive lookahead regex in JavaScript','inherit','open','open','','75-revision-10','','','2010-05-15 23:14:50','2010-05-15 22:14:50','',75,'http://www.jonathansewell.co.uk/index.php/2010/05/15/75-revision-10/',0,'revision','',0),(114,1,'2010-05-15 23:12:50','2010-05-15 22:12:50','<strong>Get the start page PageReference:</strong>\r\n<pre class=\"brush:csharp\">PageReference.StartPage</pre>\r\nA PageRefernce is basically a wrapper for integer ids. It also containsÂ convenienceÂ methods as in the above example which simply gets the start page id from the configuration:\r\n<pre class=\"brush:csharp\">EPiServer.Configuration.Settings.Instance.PageStartId</pre>\r\nThe PageData class holds information about the page such as name and URL. It makes pageÂ propertiesÂ available through the property \"Property\" (PropertyDataCollection).\r\n\r\n<strong>Get PageData from a PageReference:</strong>\r\n<pre class=\"brush:csharp\">DataFactory.Instance.GetPage(PageReference.StartPage)</pre>','EPiServer Snippets','A work in progress cheat sheet of EPiServer code snippets','inherit','open','open','','89-revision-6','','','2010-05-15 23:12:50','2010-05-15 22:12:50','',89,'http://www.jonathansewell.co.uk/index.php/2010/05/15/89-revision-6/',0,'revision','',0),(118,1,'2010-06-11 15:09:33','0000-00-00 00:00:00','I\'m setting up a new project using N2 CMS but don\'t have a clear procedure for downloading and setting up an N2 site. I\'m going to use the MVC templates example site as a starting point so make sure you have ASP.NET MVC 2 installed.\r\n<h3>Downloading the Source</h3>\r\nEither get the latest release from CodePlex atÂ Â <a href=\"http://n2cms.codeplex.com/releases/view/44446\">http://n2cms.codeplex.com/releases/view/44446</a> or get the svn repository url from the N2CMS page on Google Code atÂ <a href=\"http://code.google.com/p/n2cms/\">http://code.google.com/p/n2cms/</a> and get the latest version.Â I prefer to get the svn version because it\'s probably more up to date.Â Next, go to the \"src\"Â folder and run the batch file to build dependencies. Now open the MVC example solution in the folder \"N2.Templates.Mvc\"\r\n<h3>Some Build Errors...</h3>\r\nI got a few build errors related to missing N2 references so I just copied these into the bin folder from the src/wwwroot folder, andÂ referencedÂ them.\r\n<h3>Moving to a New Project</h3>\r\nNow I have the MVC example running I want to copy it to a new project folder and check it into a new source control repository. Copy theN2.Templates.MvcÂ folder from the \"src\" folder, Â you can use Beyond Compare so to filter out the .svn folders.\r\n\r\nI haveÂ rearrangedÂ the Â the folder structure for svn, adding trunk/branches folders, renamed wwwroot to Project.Site and added a lib folder for the project references, and an app folder for any supporting projects.Â Next, commit everything to a new svn repository, excluding the products of builds such as the bin older and contents.\r\nI\'ve also renamed the solution and project files to match the project I\'m working on, and also the assembly name and namespace for the project. Â You can use ReSharper to fix the namespaces in the source (right-click project, refactor, adjust namespaces), but you will also need to do a find and replace across the solution to make sure you change all instances of the old namespace.\r\nI also removed the namespace entries in the web.config system.web, pages, namespaces section because I like to seeÂ explicitÂ import statements, it\'s helps me understand what\'s going on. This does involve fixing the imports in pretty much every template though.\r\n<h3>Locking it down</h3>\r\nThe MVC templates site comes with a great selection of built in page types and parts, as well as example content. Obviously you need to change the example content to fit your project, but you should also disable page types and parts that are not required for the project. Although a client will happy take extra functionality, if you give it to them they\'ll expect it to work the way they want it to and you\'ll just create extra work for yourself. You can easily remove page types and parts using the N2 DisableAttribute on their class definition.\r\n<pre>[Disable]\r\npublic class FaqList : AbstractContentPage, IStructuralPage</pre>\r\n<h4>Themes</h4>\r\nIf you edit the start page in N2 you\'ll see you can select a theme from a drop-down list, this is another feature I don\'t need for this project (as it will only have one theme/design) so I\'ve removed the property from StartPage.cs\r\n<pre>[EditableThemeSelection(\"Theme\", 74, ContainerName = LayoutArea)]\r\npublic string Theme\r\n{\r\nget { return (string)(GetDetail(\"Theme\") ?? string.Empty); }\r\nset { SetDetail(\"Theme\", value); }\r\n}</pre>\r\nAnd also changed the Global.asax.cs to use the WebFormViewEngine instead of the ThemedMasterViewEngine:\r\n<pre>ViewEngines.Engines.Insert(0, new WebFormViewEngine());</pre>\r\n<h4>More things to remove</h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>The language menu from TopMenu.ascx</li>\r\n	<li>The site logo from Top.ascx</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>Organising the styles</h3>\r\nTODO\r\n<h3>Configuring TinyMCE</h3>\r\nTODO\r\n<h3>Deployment Checklist</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>set checkInstallationStatus to false in web.config (&lt;installer checkInstallationStatus=\"false\" /&gt;)</li>\r\n	<li>enable/disable globalization in web.config</li>\r\n	<li>set error reporting email address in web.config</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">References</span>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://interferencelogik.com/docs/N2CMS_TheLittleHandbook.pdf\">http://interferencelogik.com/docs/N2CMS_TheLittleHandbook.pdf</a>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://n2cms.codeplex.com/releases/view/44446\">http://n2cms.codeplex.com/releases/view/44446</a>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://code.google.com/p/n2cms/\">http://code.google.com/p/n2cms/</a>','Creating a new N2 CMS project','','draft','open','open','','','','','2010-06-11 15:09:33','2010-06-11 14:09:33','',0,'http://www.jonathansewell.co.uk/?p=118',0,'post','',0),(119,1,'2010-05-27 21:40:54','2010-05-27 20:40:54','First download the source code release from <a href=\"http://n2cms.codeplex.com/releases/view/44446\">http://n2cms.codeplex.com/releases/view/44446</a>. I\'m using the release labelled \"N2 CMS 2.0 RC2 Source Code\"\n\nMake sure you have ASP.NET MVC 2 installed.\n\nUnzip the download and run the \"Prepare Dependencies\" batch file.\n\nYou should now have an examples folder in the\n\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">References</span></strong>\n\n<a 