09-07 16:59:39','2010-09-07 15:59:39','We have our own (XCopy type) deployment process and don\'t use the EPiServer Deployment Centre or any of the installers on our web servers, as a result the scheduler service is not installed. So how do you get the EPiServer Scheduler Service installed on the web server?  Any Admin Mode page that relies on the scheduler service is showing a warning: \"The EPiServer Scheduler Service does not  appear to be active, it may have been stopped.\"\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-205\" title=\"EPiServer-scheduler-service\" src=\"http://www.jonathansewell.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2010/09/EPiServer-scheduler-service.jpg\" alt=\"EPiServer-scheduler-service\" width=\"770\" height=\"134\" />\r\n\r\nIn order to maintain maximum control over what is installed on the web server you might try to install the service using the <strong>installutil </strong>program. I tried this approach, I copied the EPiServer scheduler service files from \"C:\\Program Files (x86)\\EPiServer\\Shared\\Services\\Scheduler Service\" and ran the command:\r\n\r\n<strong>installutil EPiServer.SchedulerSvc.exe</strong>\r\n\r\nBut this doesn\'t work and you\'ll get an error:\r\n\r\n<strong>No public installers with the RunInstallerAttribute.Yes attribute could be found in the D:\\sites\\mysite\\EPiServerSchedulerService5.2.375.236\\EPiServer.SchedulerSvc.exe assembly.</strong>\r\n\r\nThe scheduler service is not designed to be manually installed like this. As such your only option is to install it using <strong>EPiServerShared.msi</strong> from the EPiServer CMS installation files (available on <a href=\"http://world.episerver.com/Download/Categories/Products/EPiServer-CMS/\">EPiServer World</a>). This will install and start 3 services and won\'t require you to restart the machine:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>EPiServer Scheduler Service</li>\r\n	<li>EPiServer CMS Log Service</li>\r\n	<li>EPiServer CMS Indexing Service</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nIt\'s not an ideal solution if you like to maintain absolute control over what is installed on the web server, but it\'s a quick and easy install that does work.','Installing the EPiServer Scheduler Service','We have our own (XCopy type) deployment process and don\'t use the EPiServer Deployment Centre or any of the installers on our web servers, as a result the scheduler service is not installed. So how do you get the EPiServer Scheduler Service installed on the web server?','publish','open','open','','installing-the-episerver-scheduler-service','','','2011-02-04 10:03:39','2011-02-04 10:03:39','',0,'http://www.jonathansewell.co.uk/?p=204',0,'post','',0),(205,1,'2010-09-07 12:27:56','2010-09-07 11:27:56','','EPiServer-scheduler-service','','inherit','open','open','','episerver-scheduler-service','','','2010-09-07 12:27:56','2010-09-07 11:27:56','',204,'http://www.jonathansewell.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2010/09/EPiServer-scheduler-service.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(206,1,'2010-09-07 12:33:15','2010-09-07 11:33:15','We\'ve just launched a new site and need to get the scheduler service up and running.  \"The EPiServer Scheduler Service does not  appear to be active, it may have been stopped.\"\n\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-205\" title=\"EPiServer-scheduler-service\" src=\"http://www.jonathansewell.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2010/09/EPiServer-scheduler-service.jpg\" alt=\"EPiServer-scheduler-service\" width=\"770\" height=\"134\" />','Installing the EPiServer Scheduler Service','','inherit','open','open','','204-revision','','','2010-09-07 12:33:15','2010-09-07 11:33:15','',204,'http://www.jonathansewell.co.uk/index.php/2010/09/07/204-revision/',0,'revision','',0),(207,1,'2010-09-07 12:37:51','2010-09-07 11:37:51','We have our own (XCopy type) deployment process and don\'t use the EPiServer Deployment Centre on our web servers, as a result the scheduler service is not installed on the web server in question. We\'ve just launched a new site and need to get the scheduler service u