Server Scheduler Service</li>\n	<li>EPiServer CMS Log Service</li>\n	<li>EPiServer CMS Indexing Service</li>\n</ul>\nIt\'s not an ideal solution if you like to maintain absolute control over what is installed on the web server, but it\'s a quick and easy install that does work.','Installing the EPiServer Scheduler Service','We have our own (XCopy type) deployment process and don\'t use the EPiServer Deployment Centre or any of the installers on our web servers, as a result the scheduler service is not installed. So how do you get the EPiServer Scheduler Service installed on the web server?','inherit','open','open','','204-revision-5','','','2010-09-07 16:59:38','2010-09-07 15:59:38','',204,'http://www.jonathansewell.co.uk/index.php/2010/09/07/204-revision-5/',0,'revision','',0),(212,1,'2010-09-08 22:23:16','2010-09-08 21:23:16','<div>\r\n\r\nI came across this when I did an upgrade from EPiServer 4 to 5, the VirtualPathPageMappingProvider showed up in the config file.\r\n\r\nIn version 4 I had an \"upload\" virtual path which was used for page files and global uploads. As part of the upgrade I separated the page files into their own folder with their own virtual path (/pages/). This creates a problem because all the links in content still point at /upload/ for page files. So you need to add:\r\n<pre class=\"brush:xml\">&lt;unifiedFileSystem&gt;\r\n	&lt;mappings&gt;\r\n		&lt;map fromPath=\"/upload\" toPath=\"/pages\" type=\"EPiServer.FileSystem.Mapping.PageDirectoryMapping,EPiServer\" /&gt;</pre>\r\nMore info here: <a href=\"../../../en/Documentation/Items/Tech-Notes/EPiServer-CMS-5/EPiServer-CMS-5-R2/EPiServer-CMS-Migration-Tool-11/#Prerequisites\">http://world.episerver.com/en/Documentation/Items/Tech-Notes/EPiServer-CMS-5/EPiServer-CMS-5-R2/EPiServer-CMS-Migration-Tool-11/#Prerequisites</a>\r\n\r\nThen during the upgrade that mapping gets converted to something like this:\r\n<pre class=\"brush:xml\">&lt;add toPath=\"~/pages/\" fromPath=\"~/upload/\" name=\"Mapping0\" type=\"EPiServer.Web.Hosting.VirtualPathPageMappingProvider,EPiServer.Legacy4\" /&gt;</pre>\r\nSo the VirtualPahPageMappingProvider is mapping requests for the path /upload/ to path /pages/, it should be last in the list of providers in the configuration if you have another provider handling the /upload/ path.\r\n\r\n</div>','Meeting the VirtualPathPageMappingProvider','I came across this when I did an upgrade from EPiServer 4 to 5, the VirtualPathPageMappingProvider showed up in the config file...','publish','open','open','','meeting-the-virtualpathpagemappingprovider','','','2011-04-07 07:09:50','2011-04-07 06:09:50','',0,'http://www.jonathansewell.co.uk/?p=212',0,'post','',0),(213,1,'2010-09-08 22:23:03','2010-09-08 21:23:03','<div>\n\nI came across this when I did an upgrade from EPiServer 4 to 5, the VirtualPathPageMappingProvider showed up in the config file.\n\nIn version 4 I had an \"upload\" virtual path which was used for page files and global uploads. As part of the upgrade I separated the page files into their own folder with their own virtual path (/pages/). This creates a problem because all the links in content still point at /upload/ for page files. So you need to add:\n<pre>&lt;unifiedFileSystem&gt;\n	&lt;mappings&gt;\n		&lt;map fromPath=\"/upload\" toPath=\"/pages\" type=\"EPiServer.FileSystem.Mapping.PageDirectoryMapping,EPiServer\" /&gt;</pre>\nMore info here: <a href=\"../../../en/Documentation/Items/Tech-Notes/EPiServer-CMS-5/EPiServer-CMS-5-R2/EPiServer-CMS-Migration-Tool-11/#Prerequisites\">http://world.episerver.com/en/Documentation/Items/Tech-Notes/EPiServer-CMS-5/EPiServer-CMS-5-R2/EPiServer-CMS-Migration-Tool-11/#Prerequisites</a>\n\nThen during the upgrade that mapping gets converted to something like this:\n<pre>&lt;add toPath=\"~/pages/\" fromPath=\"~/upload/\" name=\"Mapping0\" type=\"EPiServer.Web.Hosting.VirtualPathPageMappingProvider,EPiServer.Legacy4\" /&gt;</pre>\nSo the VirtualPahPageMappingProvider is mapping requests for the path /upload/ to path /pages/, it should be last in the list of providers in the configuration if you have another provider handling the /upload/ path.\n\n</div>','Meeting the VirtualPathPageMappingProvider','','inherit','open','open','','212-revision','','','2010-09-08 22:23:03','2010-09-08 21:23:03','',212,'http://www.jonathansewell.co.uk/index.php/2010/09/08/212-revision/',0,'revision','',0),(214,1,'2010-09-08 22:23:16','2010-09-08 21:23:16','<div>\r\n\r\nI came across this when I did an upgrade from EPiServer 4 to 5, the VirtualPathPageMappingProvider showed up in the config file.\r\n\r\nIn version 4 I had an \"upload\" virtual path which was used for page files and global uploads. As part of the upgrade I separated the page files into their own folder with their own virtual path (/pages/). This creates a problem because all the links in content still point at /upload/ for page files. So you need to add:\r\n<pre>&lt;unifiedFileSystem&gt;\r\n	&lt;mappings&gt;\r\n		&lt;map fromPath=\"/upload\" toPath=\"/pages\" type=\"EPiServer.FileSystem.Mapping.PageDirectoryMapping,EPiServer\" /&gt;</pre>\r\nMore info here: <a href=\"../../../en/Documentation/Items/Tech-Notes/EPiServer-CMS-5/EPiServer-CMS-5-R2/EPiServer-CMS-Migration-Tool-11/#Prerequisites\">http://world.episerver.com/en/Documentation/Items/Tech-Notes/EPiServer-CMS-5/EPiServer-CMS-5-R2/EPiServer-CMS-Migration-Tool-11/#Prerequisites</a>\r\n\r\nThen during the upgrade that mapping gets converted to something like this:\r\n<pre>&lt;add toPath=\"~/pages/\" fromPath=\"~/upload/\" name=\"Mapping0\" type=\"EPiServer.Web.Hosting.VirtualPathPageMappingProvider,EPiServer.Legacy4\" /&gt;</pre>\r\nSo the VirtualPahPageMappingProvider is mapping requests for the path /upload/ to path /pages/, it should be last in the list of providers in the configuration if you have another provider handling the /upload/ path.\r\n\r\n</div>','Meeting the VirtualPathPageMappingProvider','','inherit','open','open','','212-revision-2','',''