NonVisual” which contains data EPiServer CMS needs to correctly show the plug-in in edit and admin mode. Which attribute to use depends on what type of plug-in you are creating. If the plug-in has one or more buttons the “TinyMCEPluginButton” should be used, if not use “TinyMCEPluginNonVisual” attribute. <a title=\"TinyMCE Developers Guide on EPiServer World\" href=\"http://world.episerver.com/Documentation/Items/Tech-Notes/EPiServer-CMS-6/EPiServer-CMS-60/TinyMCE-Developers-Guide/\">TinyMCE Developers Guide</a></blockquote>\r\nSo I created a new class with a plugin attribute and passed in the TinyMCE configuration options to the EditorInitConfigurationOptions property.\r\n<pre class=\"brush:csharp\">[TinyMCEPluginNonVisual(AlwaysEnabled = true,\r\n	PlugInName = \"CustomTinyMceSettings\",\r\n	EditorInitConfigurationOptions =\r\n		@\"{\r\n			theme_advanced_blockformats : \'p,h3,h4,h5,h6\'\r\n		}\"\r\n	)]\r\npublic class CustomTinyMceSettings\r\n{\r\n}</pre>\r\n<a href=\"http://www.frederikvig.com/2010/10/how-to-add-support-for-iframes-and-other-elements-to-tinymce-in-episerver-cms/\">Frederik Vig</a>, <a href=\"http://www.kloojed.com/2010/05/customize-the-tiny-mce-editor-options-in-episerver-cms-6\">Marcus Lindblom</a>, and <a href=\"http://krompaco.nu/alter-default-initoptions-for-tinymce-in-episerver-6/\">Johan Kronberg</a> have covered this in blog posts.\r\n\r\nAlso check out the <a title=\"TinyMCE documentation\" href=\"http://wiki.moxiecode.com/index.php/TinyMCE:Installation\">TinyMCE </a>and <a title=\"EPiServer docs\" href=\"http://world.episerver.com/Documentation/Items/Tech-Notes/EPiServer-CMS-6/EPiServer-CMS-60/TinyMCE-Developers-Guide/\">EPiServer </a>documentation.','Remove h1 from EPiServer 6 TinyMCE','','publish','open','open','','remove-h1-from-episerver-6-tinymce','','\nhttp://krompaco.nu/alter-default-initoptions-for-tinymce-in-episerver-6/','2010-10-26 13:35:27','2010-10-26 12:35:27','',0,'http://www.jonathansewell.co.uk/?p=226',0,'post','',1),(227