l.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/EPiServer-mail-bin-changes.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"374\" height=\"766\" />\r\n\r\nThe changed files have all changed from version <strong>6.0.318.113</strong> to<strong> 6.1.79.0</strong>.\r\n<h3>Web.config Changes</h3>\r\nThese changes are too many to reproduce here so I\'ll summarise and upload the 2 config files.\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>new configuration sections registered</li>\r\n	<li>new nhibernate section</li>\r\n	<li>new hibernate-configuration section</li>\r\n	<li>new episerver.common section</li>\r\n	<li>new episerver.search section</li>\r\n	<li>new episerver.mail section</li>\r\n	<li>updated assembly bindings for updated .dll files (EPiServer.Data.Cache etc)</li>\r\n	<li>new assembly bindings (EPiServer.Mail.Core etc)</li>\r\n	<li>new role and membership providers registered (EPiServerCommonRoleProvider and EPiServerCommonMembershipProvider)</li>\r\n	<li>pages section, change enableEventValidation to false</li>\r\n	<li>new modules in &lt;system.webServer&gt;&lt;modules&gt;</li>\r\n	<li>new handlers in &lt;system.webServer&gt;&lt;handlers&gt;</li>\r\n	<li>new location sections for EPiServerMail and EPiServerMail/Public</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<a title=\"web.config before mail installation\" href=\"https://s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/js-jonathan/blog+downloads/web.config.original\">https://s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/js-jonathan/blog+downloads/web.config.original</a>\r\n\r\n<a title=\"web.config after mail installation\" href=\"https://s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/js-jonathan/blog+downloads/web.config.mail\">https://s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/js-jonathan/blog+downloads/web.config.mail</a>\r\n<ul></ul>','Install EPiServer Mail Manually','','inherit','open','open','','264-revision-12','','','2010-11-26 11:56:26','2010-11-26 11:56:26','',264,'http://www.jonathansewell.co.uk/index.php/2010/11/26/264-revision-12/',0,'revision','',0),(280,1,'2010-11-29 18:58:58','2010-11-29 18:58:58','I\'m creating a demo site of EPiServer 6 CMS using the deployment centre to create the website, then opening it in Visual Studio. That all works until I set the project to use Visual Studio\'s development server (the web server is running on IIS 6). I get a 404 error on the dashboard as soon as I switch to using the development server.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-281\" title=\"episerver-resource-not-found\" src=\"http://www.jonathansewell.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/episerver-resource-not-found.png\" alt=\"The resource cannot be found\" width=\"662\" height=\"274\" />\r\n\r\nThe problem is that the Visual Studio development server runs in classic mode (like IIS 6) and the website the Deployment Centre created is designed for Integrated Mode (IIS 7). There are apparently a few more symptoms of this including:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>EPiServer Admin Mode returning a 404 error page</li>\r\n	<li>Login page  returning a 404 error page</li>\r\n	<li>No images are shown on the site</li>\r\n	<li>The right-click context menu is not available</li>\r\n	<li>JavaScript or JQuery errors on the page</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nTo fix this I manually converted the web.config file to work for IIS 6 (massive pain in the neck!). I <strong>changed all &lt;system.webServer&gt; elements to &lt;system.web&gt; </strong>and for the sub elements, <strong>changed all &lt;handlers&gt; elements to &lt;httpHandlers&gt; and &lt;modules&gt; to &lt;httpModules&gt;</strong>. Also removed all attributes (in all child elements) except path, verb and type.\r\n\r\nI also had to add the following to &lt;httpHandlers&gt;:\r\n\r\n&lt;add path=\"*.png\" verb=\"GET,HEAD\" type=\"EPiServer.Web.StaticFileHandler, EPiServer\" /&gt;\r\n&lt;add path=\"*.jpg\" verb=\"GET,HEAD\" type=\"EPiServer.Web.StaticFileHandler, EPiServer\" /&gt;\r\n&lt;add path=\"*.jpeg\" verb=\"GET,HEAD\" type=\"EPiServer.Web.StaticFileHandler, EPiServer\" /&gt;\r\n&lt;add path=\"*.css\" verb=\"GET,HEAD\" type=\"EPiServer.Web.StaticFileHandler, EPiServer\" /&gt;\r\n&lt;add path=\"*.js\" verb=\"GET,HEAD\" type=\"EPiServer.Web.StaticFileHandler, EPiServer\" /&gt;\r\n&lt;add path=\"*.gif\" verb=\"GET,HEAD\" type=\"EPiServer.Web.StaticFileHandler, EPiServer\" /&gt;\r\n\r\nThe EPiServer installation files seem to include a version of the web.config for IIS 6 and one for IIS 7. There are located in <strong>C:\\Program Files (x86)\\EPiServer\\CMS\\6.0.530.0\\Application\\</strong> on my machine.\r\n\r\nOn a related note, you can use the AppCmd tool to migrate your web.config file from IIS6 to IIS7. (http://www.prolificnotion.co.uk/use-appcmd-to-migrate-web-config-from-iis6-to-iis7/)\r\n\r\nI found the following sites useful when looking into this:\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://world.episerver.com/Templates/Forum/Pages/thread.aspx?id=40971\">http://world.episerver.com/Templates/Forum/Pages/thread.aspx?id=40971</a>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://world.episerver.com/Templates/Forum/Pages/thread.aspx?id=40971\"></a><a href=\"http://www.markeverard.com/blog/2010/05/21/default-episerver-web-configs-for-iis6-and-iis7/\">http://www.markeverard.com/blog/2010/05/21/default-episerver-web-configs-for-iis6-and-iis7/</a>\r\n<a href=\"http://epiwiki.se/configuration/webconfig-iis7-to-iis6\"></a>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://epiwiki.se/configuration/webconfig-iis7-to-iis6\">http://epiwiki.se/configuration/webconfig-iis7-to-iis6</a>\r\n<a href=\"http://world.episerver.com/en/Documentation/Items/Tech-Notes/EPiServer-CMS-5/EPiServer-CMS-5-R2-SP1/Changes-Between-IIS6-and-IIS7/\"></a>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://world.episerver.com/en/Documentation/Items/Tech-Notes/EPiServer-CMS-5/EPiServer-CMS-5-R2-SP1/Changes-Between-IIS6-and-IIS7/\">http://world.episerver.com/en/Documentation/Items/Tech-Notes/EPiServer-CMS-5/EPiServer-CMS-5-R2-SP1/Changes-Between-IIS6-and-IIS7/</a>','EPiServer 6 in Visual Studio development server','','publish','open','open','','episerver-6-visual-studio-development-server','','\nhttp://www.markeverard.com/blog/2010/05/21/default-episerver-web-configs-for-iis6-and-iis7/','2011-04-04 16:0