am Files (x86)\\EPiServer\\CMS\\6.0.530.0\\Application\\</strong> on my machine.\n\nOn a related note, you can use the AppCmd tool to migrate your web.config file from IIS6 to IIS7. (http://www.prolificnotion.co.uk/use-appcmd-to-migrate-web-config-from-iis6-to-iis7/)\n\nI found the following sites useful when looking into this:\n\n<a href=\"http://world.episerver.com/Templates/Forum/Pages/thread.aspx?id=40971\">http://world.episerver.com/Templates/Forum/Pages/thread.aspx?id=40971</a>\n\n<a href=\"http://world.episerver.com/Templates/Forum/Pages/thread.aspx?id=40971\"></a><a href=\"http://www.markeverard.com/blog/2010/05/21/default-episerver-web-configs-for-iis6-and-iis7/\">http://www.markeverard.com/blog/2010/05/21/default-episerver-web-configs-for-iis6-and-iis7/</a>\n<a href=\"http://epiwiki.se/configuration/webconfig-iis7-to-iis6\"></a>\n\n<a href=\"http://epiwiki.se/configuration/webconfig-iis7-to-iis6\">http://epiwiki.se/configuration/webconfig-iis7-to-iis6</a>\n<a href=\"http://world.episerver.com/en/Documentation/Items/Tech-Notes/EPiServer-CMS-5/EPiServer-CMS-5-R2-SP1/Changes-Between-IIS6-and-IIS7/\"></a>\n\n<a href=\"http://world.episerver.com/en/Documentation/Items/Tech-Notes/EPiServer-CMS-5/EPiServer-CMS-5-R2-SP1/Changes-Between-IIS6-and-IIS7/\">http://world.episerver.com/en/Documentation/Items/Tech-Notes/EPiServer-CMS-5/EPiServer-CMS-5-R2-SP1/Changes-Between-IIS6-and-IIS7/</a>','EPiServer 6 in Visual Studio development server','','inherit','open','open','','280-autosave','','','2011-06-21 12:48:49','2011-06-21 11:48:49','',280,'http://www.jonathansewell.co.uk/index.php/2010/11/29/280-autosave/',0,'revision','',0),(288,1,'2010-11-29 18:58:58','2010-11-29 18:58:58','I\'m creating a demo site of EPiServer 6 CMS using the deployment centre to create the website, then opening it in Visual Studio. That all works until I set the project to use Visual Studio\'s development server (the web server is running on IIS 6). I get a 404 error on the dashboard as soon as I