 address in Git. Instructions are on GitHub <a href=\"http://help.github.com/git-email-settings/\">http://help.github.com/git-email-settings/</a>.\r\n<h2>Install PoshGit</h2>\r\nClone the PoshGit project, it\'s on GithHub at <a href=\"https://github.com/dahlbyk/posh-git\">https://github.com/dahlbyk/posh-git</a>.  Run install.ps1. If you get an error like \"the execution of scripts is disabled on this system\", make sure you Powershell execution policy is set to \"RemoteUnsigned\" using command \"Set-ExecutionPolicy RemoteUnsigned\".\r\n<h2>Configure your Merge Tool</h2>\r\nWe are using Beyond Compare 3. You can configure Git to use Beyond Compare by issuing configuration commands at the command prompt, but I prefer to paste them into the .gitconfig file (in C:\\users\\username\\ on my Windows 7 machine).\r\n<pre>[merge]\r\ntool = bc3\r\n[mergetool \"bc3\"]\r\ncmd = \\\"c:/program files/Beyond Compare 3/bcompare.exe\\\" \\\"$PWD/$LOCAL\\\" \\\"$PWD/$REMOTE\\\" \\\"$PWD/$BASE\\\" \\\"$PWD/$MERGED\\\"\r\nkeepBackup = false\r\ntrustExitCode = false</pre>','Setting up Git in Windows 7','','publish','open','open','','setting-up-git-in-windows-7','','','2011-01-22 21:40:21','2011-01-22 21:40:21','',0,'http://www.jonathansewell.co.uk/?p=304',0,'post','',0),(305,1,'2011-01-06 08:40:27','2011-01-06 08:40:27','I\'ve got a new install of Windows 7 and need to install Git. These are the steps required.\n\nI\'m following the GitHub help guide here: http://help.github.com/win-git-installation/\n<h2>Install Git for Windows (mysysgit)</h2>\nDownload and run the setup file from <a href=\"http://code.google.com/p/msysgi\">http://code.google.com/p/msysgi</a>t. Make sure to select \"<strong>Run Git from the Windows Command Prompt</strong>\" and then \"<strong>Checkout as-is, commit as-is</strong>\".','Setting up Git in Windows 7','','inherit','open','open','','304-revision','','','2011-01-06 08:40:27','2011-01-06 08:40:27','',304,'http://www.jonathansewell.co.uk/index.php/2011/01/06/304