\VPP\\Documents\"</strong> /&gt;</pre>\r\nI need to go up a directory and back down to the VPP folder, I have folder structure:\r\n\r\nD:\\LatestEPiServerProject\\VPP\\Documents\r\nD:\\LatestEPiServerProject\\Site\\\r\n\r\nThe new provider type is simply a thin wrapper that converts relative paths to physical paths that the EPiServer implementation can continue to work with.\r\n\r\nThe code is on Github at <a href=\"https://gist.github.com/778715\">https://gist.github.com/778715</a>','Use a relative path with Virtual Path Providers','','inherit','open','open','','325-revision-2','','','2011-01-13 22:17:13','2011-01-13 22:17:13','',325,'http://www.jonathansewell.co.uk/index.php/2011/01/13/325-revision-2/',0,'revision','',0),(330,1,'2011-01-06 11:24:14','2011-01-06 11:24:14','I\'ve got a new install of Windows 7 and need to install Git. These are the steps required:\r\n<h2>Install Git for Windows (mysysgit)</h2>\r\nDownload and run the setup file from <a href=\"http://code.google.com/p/msysgit\">http://code.google.com/p/msysgit</a>. Make sure to select \"<strong>Run Git from the Windows Command Prompt</strong>\" and then \"<strong>Checkout as-is, commit as-is</strong>\".  More information is in GitHub help guide http://help.github.com/win-git-installation/.\r\n<h2>Generate SSH Keys for GitHub</h2>\r\nStart the Git Bash console and follow the instructions on GitHib help <a href=\"http://help.github.com/msysgit-key-setup/\">http://help.github.com/msysgit-key-setup/</a>.  Take the public key from id_rsa.pub.  Test you can connect to github.com with the command:\r\n<pre>ssh git@github.com</pre>\r\nThis is also a good time to set your username and email address in Git. Instructions are on GitHub <a href=\"http://help.github.com/git-email-settings/\">http://help.github.com/git-email-settings/</a>.\r\n<h2>Install PoshGit</h2>\r\nClone the PoshGit project, it\'s on GithHub at <a href=\"https://github.com/dahlbyk/posh-git\">https://github.com/dahlbyk/posh-git</a>.  Run install.ps1. If you get an error like \"the execution of scripts is disabled on this system\", make sure you Powershell execution policy is set to \"RemoteUnsigned\" using command \"Set-ExecutionPolicy RemoteUnsigned\".','Setting up Git in Windows 7','','inherit','open','open','','304-revision-10','','','2011-01-06 11:24:14','2011-01-06 11:24:14','',304,'http://www.jonathansewell.co.uk/index.php/2011/01/06/304-revision-10/',0,'revision','',0),(331,1,'2011-01-23 18:14:39','2011-01-23 18:14:39','EPiServer has a page about <a title=\"EPiServer exam knowledge areas\" href=\"http://www.episerver.com/en/Education/EPiServer-Certified--Developer/Knowledge-Areas/\">the areas you need to cover for the exam</a>.\n\nThere is <a href=\"http://stackoverflow.com/questions/556221\">a Stackoverflow thread about the version 5 exam</a> that has some useful information.\n\n<strong>Some blog posts about the exam:</strong>\n\nEPiServer 6 Exam Sections\n\n<a title=\"Rouslan Minasian\'s post\" href=\"http://world.episerver.com/Blogs/Rouslan-Minasian/Dates/2010/8/EPiServer-Certification/\">EPiServer Certification</a>, Rouslan Minasian\n\n<a title=\"Fredrick Haglund\'s post\" href=\"http://blog.fredrikhaglund.se/blog/2008/11/30/how-to-become-a-episerver-ceritified-developer/\">How to become a EPiServer Ceritified Developer</a>, Fredrik Haglund.\n\n<a title=\"Mikael Lundin\'s post\" href=\"http://mint.litemedia.se/2008/11/29/episerver-cms-5-certified-developer/\">EPiServer CMS 5 Certified Developer</a>, Mikael Lundin\n\n<a title=\"Björn Sållarp\'s post\" href=\"http://blog.sallarp.com/episerver-cms-5-certified/\">EPiServer CMS 5 Certified!</a>, Björn Sållarp\n\nWhen I was preparing for the exam I re-read the administrator and editor manuals, the developer documentation in the SDK, and the tech notes. The tech notes form the bulk of the material and there are a lot of them so it\'s worth prioritising them somehow.','EPiServer 6 exam bookmarks','','inherit','open','open','','294-autosave','','','2011-01-23 18:14:39','2011-01-23 18:14:39','',294,'http://www.jonathansewell.co.uk/index.php/2011/01/23/294-autosave/',0,'revision','',0),(332,1,'2010-09-07 16:59:39','2010-09-07 15:59:39','We have our own (XCopy type) deployment process and don\'t use the EPiServer Deployment Centre or any of the installers on our web servers, as a result the scheduler service is not installed. So how do you get the EPiServer Scheduler Service installed on the web server?  Any Admin Mode page that relies on the scheduler service is showing a warning: \"The EPiServer Scheduler Service does not  appear to be active, it may have been stopped.\"\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-205\" title=\"EPiServer-scheduler-service\" src=\"http://www.jonathansewell.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2010/09/EPiServer-scheduler-service.jpg\" alt=\"EPiServer-scheduler-service\" width=\"770\" height=\"134\" />\r\n\r\nIn order to maintain maximum control over what is installed on the web server you might try to install the service using the <strong>installutil </strong>program. I tried this approach, I copied the EPiServer scheduler service files from \"C:\\Program Files (x86)\\EPiServer\\Shared\\Services\\Scheduler Service\" and ran the command:\r\n\r\n<strong>installutil EPiServer.SchedulerSvc.exe</strong>\r\n\r\nBut this doesn\'t work and you\'ll get an error:\r\n\r\n<strong>No public installers with the RunInstallerAttribute.Yes attribute could be found in the D:\\sites\\jisc-collections.ac.uk\\EPiServerSchedulerService5.2.375.236\\EPiServer.SchedulerSvc.exe assembly.</strong>\r\n\r\nThe scheduler service is not designed to be manually installed like this. As such your only option is to install it using <strong>EPiServerShared.msi</strong> from the EPiServer CMS installation files (available on <a href=\"http://world.episerver.com/Download/Categories/Products/EPiServer-CMS/\">EPiServer World</a>). This will install and start 3 services and won\'t require you to restart the machine:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>EPiServer Scheduler Service</li>\r\n	<li>EPiServer CMS Log Service</li>\r\n	<li>EPiServer CMS Indexing Service</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nIt\'s not an ideal solution if you like to maintain absolute control over what is installed on the web server, but it\'s a quick and easy install that does work.','Installing the EPiServer Scheduler Service','We have our own (XCopy type) deployment process and don\'t use the EPiServer Deployment Centre or any of the installers on our web servers, as a result the scheduler service is not installed. So how do you get the EPiServer Scheduler Service installed on the web server?','inherit','open','open','','204-revision-6','','','2010-09-07 16:59:39','2010-09-07 15:59:39','',204,'http://www.jonathansewell.co.uk/index.php/2010/09/07/204-revision-6/',0,'revision','',0),(333,1,'2011-04-03 19:21:39','2011-04-03 18:21:39',' ','','','publish','open','open','','333','','','2011-04-07 07:08:04','2011-04-07 06:08:04','',0,'http://www.jonathansewell.co.uk/?p=333',1,'nav_menu_item','',0),(334,1,'2011-04-03 19:21:39','2011-04-03 18:21:39',' ','','','publish','open','open','','334','','','2011-04-07 07:08:04','2011-04-07 06:08:04','',0,'http://www.jonathansewell.co.uk/?p=334',2,'nav_menu_item','',0),(335,1,'2011-04-03 19:21:39','2011-04-03 18:21:39',' ','','','publish','open','open','','335','','','2011-04-07 07:08:04','2011-04-07 06:08:04','',0,'http://www.jonathansewell.co.uk/?p=335',3,'nav_menu_item','',0),(336,1,'2011-04-03 19:37:20','0000-00-00 00:00:00','This is my web development learning journal. It&#8217;s a place for me to store useful code and information that I work with so I can refer back to it in the future. It&#8217;s also a learning tool because writing down a problem or solution makes me think about it logically and helps me to understand it.\r\n\r\nI&#8217;m a web developer and I work at Cubeworks in Brighton.\r\n\r\n','','','draft','open','open','','','','','2011-04-03 19:37:20','0000-00-00 00:00:00','',0,'http://www.jonathansewell.co.u