','Disqus/1.1(2.52):100620344','',0,0),(216,50,'Coach bags','','http://www.coachbagshandbags.com','117.23.236.171','2010-11-23 12:25:16','2010-11-23 12:25:16','<strong>...</strong>\n\nExtremely inspiring write-up, Thanks !...',0,'0','Opera/9.64(Windows NT 5.1; U; en) Presto/2.1.1','trackback',0,0),(217,257,'Malin Engdahl','malin.engdahl@episerver.com','','','2010-11-25 20:22:00','2010-11-25 20:22:00','Thank you very much for your input. That is exactly why we do sneak previews – to get early feedback from you guys.\r\n\r\nFirst of all, this feature obviously requires some additional explanation than was written in Allan’s blog post.\r\n\r\nThere are two different ways the “mark as in use” feature works, explicitly and automatically.\r\n\r\nYou are right that there should be an automatic version of this feature, which is included in this release. It works by piggy-backing the auto save function where editors are notified when an someone else’s auto save version of the page is detected. The reason for waiting until the first auto save (for which the default setting is one minute), is to avoid locking the page when somebody might just be browsing the web tree.\r\n\r\nBut we wanted to take this piece of functionality one step further – sometimes editors might be working on a page offline (in Microsoft Word for example). The editor will then want to mark the page as in use for other editors to know. This is where the explicit version of the new feature comes in handy.\r\n\r\nIn your blog post it was mentioned that it was not a good idea with a lock that isn’t really a lock. Input from users suggests there was no demand for a lock. Hence we call it “Mark as in use” to indicate that it is not a lock.\r\n\r\nOn-page edit was decided to not support this feature, in order to keep the scope down. But you might see it in a future release.\r\n\r\nOur intention is to listen to our users as much as possible. We will gladly listen to your input which will help us further improving this and other features.\r\n\r\nRegards\r\nMalin Engdahl\r\nUX Manager, EPiServer',0,'1','Disqus/1.1(2.52):102849579','',0,0),(218,257,'Jonathan Sewell','','http://twitter.com/jonathansewell','','2010-11-25 21:25:00','2010-11-25 21:25:00','Hi Malin\n\nThanks for your feedback on my post. It\'s good to hear that there is an automatic mechanism for marking a page as in use. Although I don\'t understand the reason for the 1 minute wait, surely if someone opens a page in edit mode and opens the edit tab you could say they are editing right away, not after 1 minute. I\'m imagining it should work like Zendesk\'s \"Agent Collision\" (https://support.zendesk.com/entries/247713-introducing-agent-collision).\n\nIt\'s difficult to comment on a system that I haven\'t actually tried and it\'ll probably make more sense when I have it in front of me, so I\'m looking forward to the next release.',0,'1','Disqus/1.1(2.52):102889923','',217,0),(219,50,'Chanel bags','','http://www.chanelhandbagsbags.com','113.140.198.245','2010-11-26 07:49:51','2010-11-26 07:49:51','<strong>...</strong>\n\nHi! Your publish rocks and is a excellent understand!...',0,'0','Opera/9.64(Windows NT 5.1; U; en) Presto/2.1.1','trackback',0,0),(220,50,'Chanel shoes','','http://www.chanelbootsshoes.com','222.91.241.141','2010-11-30 17:00:24','2010-11-30 17:00:24','<strong>...</strong>\n\nCertain glad that I navigated for a page by accident. I’ll be subscribing to your feed to ensure I can get the newest updates. Enjoy all the facts below...',0,'0','Opera/9.64(Windows NT 5.1; U; en) Presto/2.1.1','trackback',0,0),(221,50,'Moncler jackets','','http://www.us-moncleroutletn.com','117.23.237.63','2010-12-02 13:23:48','2010-12-02 13:23:49','<strong>...</strong>\n\nIt\'s a great place!...',0,'0','Mozilla/5.0 (Windows; U; Windows NT 5.1; de; rv:1.9.1.3) Gecko/20090824 Firefox/3.5.3 (.NET CLR 3.5.30729)','trackback',0,0),(222,50,'Gucci watches','','http://www.guccioutletwatches.com','222.91.241.75','2010-12-07 02:49:11','